comment: Rays : Definition 6.1 of [Schwabhauser] p. 43. With this definition, ` A ( K `` C ) B ` means that ` A ` and ` B ` are on the same ray with initial point ` C ` . This follows the same notation as Schwabhauser where rays are first defined as a relation. It is possible to recover the ray itself using e.g. ` ( ( K `` C ) " { A } ) ` (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 21-Dec-2019.)
